sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K136040
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Promoter of flgA gene from E. coli flagella
flgA is a class 2 gene that is part of the construction of the flagella ( Ordering Genes in a Flagella Pathway by Analysis of Expression Kinetics from Living Bacteria - S. Kalir, J. McClure, K. Pabbaraju, C. Southward, M. Ronen, S. Leibler, M. G. Surette, U. Alon ).
Its promoter is consitutively repressed.
It is activated by FlhD4C2 and maybe by FliA with different strength ( Using a Quantitative Blueprint to Reprogram the Dynamics of the Flagella Gene Network - Shiraz Kalir and Uri Alon ).
flgA promotor is here followed by RFP.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: alexandra bouaziz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: flgA promotor comes from E. coli K12 strain MG1655.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: pFlgA was digested by EcoRI ,SpeI (FI )and cloned into the J61002 plasmid containing RFP (BV).

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J61002
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Plasmid for construction of promoter basic parts. Insertion of a promoter element between XbaI and SpeI sites results in a RFP reporter while retaining the ability to do biobrick assembly. Part J61002 is the tet promoter variant of the plasmid.
